Alleged gangsters seem to be holding Bishop Lavis hostage. The trenches are being dug by a network company -- all that’s missing is the fibre. But now the fibre installation sub-contractor seems to have pulled out after a meeting with alleged extortionists. eNCA's Monique Mortlock reports. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Over 100 job opportunities lost and a Cape Town community without fibre, all thanks to alleged gangsters. A contractor that was supposed to install fibre in Bishop Lavis -- a first for the community -- was allegedly facing threats of extortion. Now, the company has pulled out of the area. The SAPS says it’s investigating, although no official complaints were made. * eNCA's Monique Mortlock reports.